    "blocks": [
        {
            "id": 44,
            "sort_order": 10,
            "published": true,
            "data": {
                "title": "How A1Z26 works",
                "text": "<p>A1Z26 is a simple letter-to-number substitution system where each letter is replaced by its position in the alphabet. In English, A=1, B=2, C=3, and so on until Z=26.</p><p>During encoding, text is converted into a sequence of numbers. During decoding, the numbers are converted back into letters using the selected alphabet.</p><p>A1Z26 is commonly used in educational exercises, puzzles, treasure hunts, escape rooms, and beginner cryptography challenges.</p>"
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 62,
            "sort_order": 20,
            "published": true,
            "data": {
                "title": "Letter–Number Reference (English Alphabet)",
